# =============================================================================
# rentalAppLedger — Bootstrap Configuration Template
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   cp bootstrap/.env.example bootstrap/.env
#   Fill in your real values in bootstrap/.env
#   bash bootstrap/bootstrap.sh
#
# RULES:
#   bootstrap/.env         → gitignored, holds real values, NEVER commit
#   bootstrap/.env.example → committed, safe template only
#
# KODEKLOUD CONSTRAINTS (hard limits that cannot be worked around):
#   - Cannot create or modify role definitions / assignments (BLOCKED)
#   - Cannot create additional resource groups (BLOCKED)
#   - Cannot elevate access (BLOCKED)
#   - Cannot purchase marketplace items (BLOCKED)
#   - Cannot access billing / cost information (BLOCKED)
#   - Lab user CLI login fails due to MFA / conditional access (use az login)
#   - SP client secret expires every KodeKloud session
#   - KodeKloud internally pre-grants the SP Contributor access to the RG
# =============================================================================

# ── Cloud selection ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Valid values: azure | gcp | both
# Put the value alone — no inline comments on the same line
CLOUD=azure

# ── GitHub ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GITHUB_ORG=<your-github-username-or-org>
GITHUB_REPO=AI-RentalApp-Ledger

# =============================================================================
# AZURE — KodeKloud Lab
#
# Auth strategy for GitHub Actions:
#   PRIMARY  : OIDC via federated credentials on the pre-existing SP (no secret)
#   FALLBACK : Client secret on the pre-existing SP (expires each lab session)
#
# Bootstrap login:
#   bootstrap.sh checks `az account show` — if no active session it prints
#   instructions to run `az login` in the browser and exits.
#   Do NOT put your password here; az login handles it interactively.
#
# Pre-existing SP (KodeKloud provides this — do NOT create a new one):
#   APP_ID : 8f4772d5-9056-4f3a-98e6-d0fb30d9592b
#   Access : KodeKloud internally pre-grants Contributor on the RG; do NOT
#            attempt role assignments — they will be rejected.
# =============================================================================

# ── Required ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Your KodeKloud lab subscription UUID
AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID="a2b28c85-1948-4263-90ca-bade2bac4df4"

# Pre-existing resource group created by KodeKloud for your lab
AZURE_RG="kml_rg_main-11e71125c90a4f0a"

# Region — KodeKloud allows: eastus | westus | centralus | southcentralus
AZURE_LOCATION="eastus"

# Tenant — use the domain form, NOT the GUID (avoids AADSTS90002 errors)
AZURE_TENANT_ID="azurekmlprodkodekloud.onmicrosoft.com"

# Pre-existing SP app (client) ID — DO NOT change; KodeKloud pre-grants access
AZURE_APP_ID="8f4772d5-9056-4f3a-98e6-d0fb30d9592b"

# ── Optional — Client Secret fallback ─────────────────────────────────────────
# If OIDC federated credentials cannot be added to the SP, set this to the
# client secret you generated for the SP in Azure Portal.
# Leave blank to skip the client-secret section of the secrets output.
# WARNING: expires every KodeKloud lab session — regenerate each time.
AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ── Optional — Lab username (informational only, not used for login) ──────────
# The bootstrap script does NOT attempt non-interactive login.
# These fields are here for your reference / copy-paste only.
AZURE_LAB_USERNAME="kk_lab_user_main-11e71125c90a4f0a@azurekmlprodkodekloud.onmicrosoft.com"

# ── Optional — Debug ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to 1 to print all loaded .env values at startup (passwords masked)
BOOTSTRAP_DEBUG=0

# =============================================================================
# GCP — KodeKloud pre-provides project; fill from lab dashboard
# =============================================================================

# GCP project ID (run: gcloud config get-value project)
GCP_PROJECT_ID=<your-gcp-project-id>

# GCP lab service account email (pre-created by KodeKloud, if provided)
# Leave blank if KodeKloud does not pre-create one — script will create it
GCP_LAB_SA_EMAIL=

# Region — KodeKloud: US regions only
GCP_REGION=us-central1

# =============================================================================
# GitHub Secrets checklist — copy these values after bootstrap completes
# GitHub → Repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# =============================================================================
#
# AZURE — Option A: OIDC (preferred, no expiry):
#   AZURE_CLIENT_ID        = AZURE_APP_ID above
#   AZURE_TENANT_ID        = AZURE_TENANT_ID above
#   AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID  = AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID above
#   TF_BACKEND_RG          = AZURE_RG above
#   TF_BACKEND_SA          = printed by bootstrap.sh after run
#   TF_BACKEND_CONTAINER   = tfstate
#
# AZURE — Option B: Client Secret fallback (expires each lab session):
#   AZURE_CLIENT_ID        = AZURE_APP_ID above
#   AZURE_TENANT_ID        = AZURE_TENANT_ID above
#   AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID  = AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID above
#   AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET    = AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET above
#   TF_BACKEND_RG          = AZURE_RG above
#   TF_BACKEND_SA          = printed by bootstrap.sh after run
#   TF_BACKEND_CONTAINER   = tfstate
#
# GCP:
#   GCP_PROJECT_ID                  = from above
#   GCP_WORKLOAD_IDENTITY_PROVIDER  = printed by bootstrap.sh after run
#   GCP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT             = printed by bootstrap.sh after run
#   TF_BACKEND_BUCKET               = printed by bootstrap.sh after run
#
# Notifications (all optional):
#   DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL    = https://discord.com/api/webhooks/<id>/<token>
#   SMTP_PASSWORD          = <gmail-app-password>
#   MAIL_TO                = alerts@yourdomain.com
#   GROQ_API_KEY           = <groq-free-tier-key>
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY      = <claude-api-key>
